    <h1>Chapter 4: Application Package</h1>

    <h2>MS-Word (Word Processor)</h2>
    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
        MS-Word is a text editing or word processing software developed by Microsoft Corporation, USA, under the MS-Office package. Word processing refers to the use of a computer to create, edit, and print documents. A word processor enables us to create a document, store it electronically on a disk, display it on a screen, modify it using commands from the keyboard, and print it on a printer. MS-Word is a Windows-based application with many powerful features to manipulate documents. With this program, we can create various types of documents like letters, reports, theses, manuals, brochures, advertisements, and many others. Besides creating, editing, and modifying documents, MS-Word provides special facilities such as checking spelling and grammatical errors, searching for synonyms and antonyms, working with columns, tables, special symbols, pictures, graphs, charts, and more. Documents created with MS-Word have a “.doc” extension, while newer versions have the extension “.docx”.
    </p>

    <h3>Features of MS-Word</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Fast operation:</strong> MS-Word operates faster since it is digital text editing software without mechanical movement.</li>
        <li><strong>Editing text feature (Character formatting):</strong> Easily insert, delete, modify documents, and customize text styles.</li>
        <li><strong>Permanet storage:</strong> Documents can be stored electronically on disks for later retrieval.</li>
        <li><strong>Graphics:</strong> Allows insertion of objects like pictures and graphs anywhere in the document.</li>
        <li><strong>OLE (Object Linking and Embedding):</strong> Technology used to share information between programs through objects.</li>
        <li><strong>Mail merge:</strong> Tool to produce multiple letters, labels, and envelopes using information stored in lists or databases.</li>
        <li><strong>Searching:</strong> Allows searching for words or text and replacing or deleting them throughout the document.</li>
        <li><strong>Printing:</strong> Users can print documents anytime.</li>
        <li><strong>Formatting a document:</strong> Tools to enhance document appearance for readability and attractiveness.</li>
        <li><strong>Spelling and Grammar checker:</strong> Identifies spelling and grammatical errors with colored wavy lines.</li>
        <li><strong>Use of thesaurus:</strong> Helps to look up synonyms and antonyms quickly.</li>
    </ul>
    <div style="text-align: center;">
